    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="441" subtype="editorial-note"
                type="document" xml:id="d441">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>No official record of the conversation at this meeting has been found. <persName
                        corresp="#p_LWD1">Leahy</persName>, p. 214, writes: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“… President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> on December
                            4 gave a dinner in honor of the Turkish President. It was an interesting
                            affair, all the conversation being in French, which the President spoke
                            without hesitation.</p>
                        <p>“After the dinner, the Prime Minister joined the party and promptly laid
                            siege to President <persName corresp="#p_II1">Inonu</persName> to induce
                            him to cast the fate of his country with the Allies. <persName
                                corresp="#p_CC2">Churchill</persName> did most of the talking.
                                <persName corresp="#p_II1">Inonu</persName> just listened. Later,
                            the President told his British colleague that if he, <persName
                                corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName>, were a Turk, he would
                            require more assurance of aid than Britain had promised before
                            abandoning neutrality and leading his nation into war.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0803" n="699" xml:id="pg_699"/>
                <p>The list of those present is derived from the Log, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>,
                        <ref target="#pg_657">p. 657</ref>, which includes <persName
                        corresp="#p_CC2">Churchill</persName> in the dinner list. The second Russian
                    listed is presumably <persName corresp="#p_MSS1">Sergey Sergeyevich
                        Mikhailov</persName>, of the Soviet Embassy at Ankara.</p>
            </div>
